Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Cream butter and confectioners' sugar together. Add the cornstarch and flour and mix well. Stir in the chopped cherries. Drop teaspoonfuls of the dough onto a cookie sheet then press with tines of a floured fork. Bake at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C) until lightly golden, about 10 to 15 minutes.